	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">Dwedit wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Here's a little feedback about gameplay:<br />The razor line is much better than the gun, since you can't hit low enemies with the gun, but you can hit them with the razor line.<br />Also, not being able to drop down from platforms with A+Down seems strange.</div><br /><br />Thanks,   The weapons all have pros and cons.<br />I also generally use the razor line unless an enemy is far away, or not easily approachable: e.g. for the madman of the subway boss, or the banshee.  The rolly balls make Miura easier.<br /><br />As far as dropping down, I considered it, but decided to go with using a+down as a way to stay in one spot and aim in any direction.  If I were to switch to drop down, I think it would only be for the platforms you can travel upwards through. (similar to how Bionic Commando has 2 platform types)

		

		</td>
	</tr>
